The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Sex case on minister
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           Sex case on minister
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Thiruvananthapuram, Dec. 10: A magistrate today directed police to register a case against Kerala health minister P.K. Sreemathy, her son and two others accused in a sex scandal involving a minor.         
	Chief judicial magistrate Philip Thomas issued the directive on a petition filed by C. Nagaraj, a lawyer. He cited revelations by V.S. Achuthanandans former aide K. Suresh Kumar that the case file had been suppressed by two officials in the chief ministers office  his private secretary S. Rajendran and political secretary K.N. Balagopal.         
	A girl from Kililoor near Kottayam had allegedly been dragged into a sex racket after being promised roles in television serials. She became pregnant and died of infection after delivery in November 2004.                                                                                                                                                                          
